These conditions affect Digimon during battle.

{fc9Digimon can only be affected by one at a time, although existing
status abnormalities may be overwritten by more powerful ones.}
Icons will be displayed next to stats affected by a status abnormality.

{fc9Please refer to "Status Abnormality Types & Effects" for more details.}

This is a special status change during battle.

{fc9It reverses favorable and unfavorable Attributes and Elements. 
The effect is continuous throughout the battle.}

{fc9Poison}
The Digimon incurs poison damage at the end of its turn. It can
be cured immediately using items or skills.

{fc9Deadly Poison}
The Digimon incurs significant poison damage at the end of its
turn. It can be cured immediately using items or skills.

{fc9Confusion}
The Digimon may not be able to perform any actions during its turn.
It can recover immediately using items or skills.

{fc9Chaos}
The Digimon is unable to perform any actions during its turn. It can
recover when attacked, or by using items or skills.
